images.alt: A bustling open-air marketplace stretches precariously along the rim of an immense vertical chasm carved into orange desert stone. The abyss yawns dark and endless at the center, its sheer walls plummeting straight down into obscurity, with distant birds circling far below. Merchants and townsfolk crowd the edges, their stalls shaded by white and red striped awnings that ripple in the sunlit breeze. Stacks of goods, baskets of produce, and clay jars are arranged dangerously close to the precipice, where even a single misstep could mean a fatal fall. The surrounding city rises in the background with pale blue and stone-colored buildings pressed close together, their facades weathered by time and heat. Despite the perilous setting, life continues in vivid detail: figures haggle, children weave between crowds, and animals roam among the stalls, all against the overwhelming presence of the bottomless gulf that splits the heart of the marketplace.
